	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You hold a forked twig in the air, repeating the name of the creature you're looking for. With a few hand gestures, the twig hones in on the creature you're looking for, bending and pulling your arm gently in their direction.</em></p><p><strong>Utility Spell</strong></p><ul><li><p>Describe and name a creature that you are familiar with: either a specific creature (Lady Gabrielle of Fallow) or the nearest creature of a certain ancestry (the nearest dwarf). You must be familiar with the chosen creature or type of creature. You don't need line of sight to the target.</p></li><li><p>You sense the closest creature who meets the requirements that you state.</p></li><li><p>You know where the creature is, relative to you. If the creature is in motion, you know the direction of their movement.</p></li><li><p>You cannot locate a creature who is shapeshifted (or transformed via magic like<em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.wfPXFotkHWY7laah]{Polymorph}</em>) into a different form than you are expecting.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Upcasting:</strong> Range increases by 500 feet for each spell level above 2nd.</p><p></p><p><em>This spell can't locate a creature if any thickness of lead, even a thin sheet, blocks a direct path between you and the target.</em></p>",
